   "source": [
    "# Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) — PathMNIST\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook explores the PathMNIST dataset from the MedMNIST collection.\n",
    "PathMNIST is a 9-class classification task for colorectal cancer histopathology,\n",
    "derived from the NCT-CRC-HE-100K dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objectives:**\n",
    "- Understand dataset size, structure, and splits\n",
    "- Analyze class distributions across train/val/test\n",
    "- Visualize sample images from each class\n",
    "- Examine pixel intensity distributions\n",
    "- Inform preprocessing and augmentation decisions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '..')\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "from medmnist import PathMNIST\n",
    "from torchvision import transforms\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.dataset import CLASS_NAMES, get_raw_dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_style('whitegrid')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 120\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Libraries loaded successfully.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Dataset Overview"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load raw datasets (without normalization for visualization)\n",
    "train_ds, val_ds, test_ds = get_raw_dataset(data_dir='../data', image_size=224)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'PathMNIST Dataset Summary')\n",
    "print(f'========================')\n",
    "print(f'Number of classes: {len(CLASS_NAMES)}')\n",
    "print(f'Image size: 224 x 224 x 3 (RGB)')\n",
    "print(f'Train samples: {len(train_ds):,}')\n",
    "print(f'Validation samples: {len(val_ds):,}')\n",
    "print(f'Test samples: {len(test_ds):,}')\n",
    "print(f'Total samples: {len(train_ds) + len(val_ds) + len(test_ds):,}')\n",
    "print(f'\\nClass names:')\n",
    "for i, name in enumerate(CLASS_NAMES):\n",
    "    print(f'  {i}: {name}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Class Distribution Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_label_counts(dataset):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Extract label counts from a dataset.\"\"\"\n",
    "    labels = []\n",
    "    for _, label in dataset:\n",
    "        labels.append(label.item() if hasattr(label, 'item') else int(label))\n",
    "    return Counter(labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "train_counts = get_label_counts(train_ds)\n",
    "val_counts = get_label_counts(val_ds)\n",
    "test_counts = get_label_counts(test_ds)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build summary DataFrame\n",
    "summary_data = []\n",
    "for i in range(len(CLASS_NAMES)):\n",
    "    summary_data.append({\n",
    "        'Class': CLASS_NAMES[i],\n",
    "        'Train': train_counts.get(i, 0),\n",
    "        'Val': val_counts.get(i, 0),\n",
    "        'Test': test_counts.get(i, 0),\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(summary_data)\n",
    "df['Total'] = df['Train'] + df['Val'] + df['Test']\n",
    "df['Train %'] = (df['Train'] / df['Train'].sum() * 100).round(1)\n",
    "print(df.to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize class distribution\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, (split_name, counts) in zip(axes, [('Train', train_counts), ('Validation', val_counts), ('Test', test_counts)]):\n",
    "    classes = list(range(len(CLASS_NAMES)))\n",
    "    values = [counts.get(c, 0) for c in classes]\n",
    "    colors = plt.cm.tab10(np.linspace(0, 1, len(CLASS_NAMES)))\n",
    "    ax.bar(classes, values, color=colors)\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('Class Index')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Count')\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'{split_name} Set Distribution (n={sum(values):,})')\n",
    "    ax.set_xticks(classes)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../results/class_distribution.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": 
### Interpretation
The class distribution across training, validation, and test sets appears relatively consistent, indicating that the dataset splits are well-structured. 
While there is some variation in class frequency, no single class dominates the dataset.
This suggests that the model is less likely to suffer from severe class imbalance, though evaluation metrics such as F1-score remain important for accounting for subtle differences in class representation.[
    "## 3. Sample Image Visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display sample images for each class\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 3, figsize=(12, 12))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Group training samples by class\n",
    "class_samples = {i: [] for i in range(len(CLASS_NAMES))}\n",
    "for img, label in train_ds:\n",
    "    lbl = label.item() if hasattr(label, 'item') else int(label)\n",
    "    if len(class_samples[lbl]) < 1:\n",
    "        class_samples[lbl].append(img)\n",
    "    if all(len(v) >= 1 for v in class_samples.values()):\n",
    "        break\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):\n",
    "    if i < len(CLASS_NAMES) and class_samples[i]:\n",
    "        img = class_samples[i][0].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()\n",
    "        ax.imshow(img)\n",
    "        ax.set_title(f'{i}: {CLASS_NAMES[i]}', fontsize=10)\n",
    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Sample Images from Each Class', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../results/sample_images.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": 
### Interpretation: Visual inspection of the dataset reveals clear structural differences between certain tissue types, such as adipose and tumor regions. 
However, some classes exhibit overlapping visual characteristics, particularly in texture and staining patterns. 
This overlap may increase classification difficulty and highlights the importance of robust feature extraction and data augmentation.[
    "## 4. Pixel Intensity Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Analyze pixel intensity statistics across channels\n",
    "n_samples = min(1000, len(train_ds))\n",
    "pixel_values = {'R': [], 'G': [], 'B': []}\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(n_samples):\n",
    "    img, _ = train_ds[i]\n",
    "    pixel_values['R'].extend(img[0].numpy().flatten())\n",
    "    pixel_values['G'].extend(img[1].numpy().flatten())\n",
    "    pixel_values['B'].extend(img[2].numpy().flatten())\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 4))\n",
    "colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue']\n",
    "for ax, (channel, values), color in zip(axes, pixel_values.items(), colors):\n",
    "    ax.hist(values, bins=50, color=color, alpha=0.7, density=True)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'{channel} Channel')\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('Pixel Intensity')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Density')\n",
    "    mean_val = np.mean(values)\n",
    "    std_val = np.std(values)\n",
    "    ax.axvline(mean_val, color='black', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean={mean_val:.3f}')\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Pixel Intensity Distribution (first 1000 training images)', fontsize=13)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../results/pixel_distribution.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Channel Statistics (normalized to [0,1]):')\n",
    "for ch in ['R', 'G', 'B']:\n",
    "    vals = np.array(pixel_values[ch])\n",
    "    print(f'  {ch}: mean={vals.mean():.4f}, std={vals.std():.4f}, min={vals.min():.4f}, max={vals.max():.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": 
### Interpretation
The pixel intensity distributions vary across the RGB channels, reflecting differences in staining and tissue composition. 
The relatively wide spread of values supports the use of normalization to stabilize model training.
These observations also justify the use of color-based augmentations, such as color jitter, to improve generalization across varying staining conditions.[
    "## 5. Data Augmentation Preview"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.dataset import get_transforms\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show augmented versions of a single image\n",
    "raw_transform = transforms.Compose([transforms.ToTensor()])\n",
    "raw_ds = PathMNIST(split='train', transform=raw_transform, download=True, root='../data', size=224)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get a sample PIL image\n",
    "sample_img_tensor, sample_label = raw_ds[0]\n",
    "sample_pil = transforms.ToPILImage()(sample_img_tensor)\n",
    "\n",
    "aug_transform = transforms.Compose([\n",
    "    transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(p=0.5),\n",
    "    transforms.RandomVerticalFlip(p=0.5),\n",
    "    transforms.RandomRotation(degrees=15),\n",
    "    transforms.ColorJitter(brightness=0.2, contrast=0.2, saturation=0.2, hue=0.1),\n",
    "    transforms.ToTensor(),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 4, figsize=(16, 8))\n",
    "axes[0, 0].imshow(sample_pil)\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_title('Original')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "for idx, ax in enumerate(axes.flat[1:], 1):\n",
    "    aug_img = aug_transform(sample_pil).permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()\n",
    "    ax.imshow(aug_img)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'Augmented #{idx}')\n",
    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Data Augmentation Examples', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../results/augmentation_preview.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Key EDA Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "### Summary\n",
    "- **Dataset**: PathMNIST (colorectal cancer histopathology, 9 classes)\n",
    "- **Image dimensions**: 224 x 224 x 3 (RGB)\n",
    "- **Splits**: Train / Validation / Test with standard MedMNIST partitions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Observations\n",
    "1. **Class Imbalance**: The dataset shows moderate variation in class frequencies, but no extreme imbalance is present. This motivates the use of weighted loss or careful metric selection (F1, macro averages).\n",
    "2. **Visual Diversity**: Different tissue types have distinct visual patterns — e.g., adipose tissue shows clear fat cell boundaries, while debris appears as amorphous staining.\n",
    "3. **Color Variation**: Histopathology images show variation in staining intensity, which justifies using color jitter augmentation.\n",
    "4. **Preprocessing Decisions**:\n",
    "   - Use ImageNet normalization (images are natural-looking RGB histopathology patches)\n",
    "   - Apply geometric augmentation (flip, rotate) since tissue orientation is arbitrary\n",
    "   - Apply color jitter to account for staining variability\n",
    "\n",
    "These findings inform our model training pipeline and augmentation strategy."
   ]
  }
